ip addr - view ip addresses
ip route -  view routing table
netstat -  show active connections,routing tables,interface statistics,multicast memberships.
ss - socket statistics (It is faster and powerful than netstat)
ping - test connectivity to another host
traceroute - show the route packets take to a network host  
curl - transfer data from or to a server (eg: curl http://example.com ...it retrieves the content of the webpage)
scp - secure copy files between hosts on a network  (scp source_file user@remote_host:destination_path)
ssh - secure shell to remotely access another machine (ssh user@remote_host) 